          What is the difference between manual and automated testing?
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a" style="display:block;">Manual testing involves a human tester manually exploring and evaluating your application, which is great for catching usability issues and edge cases. Automated testing uses scripts to run repetitive tests quickly and consistently, making it ideal for regression testing and continuous integration. We use a combination of both to provide comprehensive coverage.</div>
      </div>
